A Playstation computer and a recent television were among other debris on earth - the victims of Icelandic summer wetness.
It was open into the old office of Háskólaprents and there were a lot of cats to smell.
It is clear that someone has nestled around in one corner but no one is visible.
Stacks of sofas and beds and a few pallets of geological pages, no doubt about to become a book, blew up.
